REFERENCE DOCUMENTATION ONLY -- NOT A BUILD INPUT.

This unified diff shows the equivalent customization expressed as a
patch against GoogleCloudPlatform/DataflowTemplates'
Cloud_Spanner_Change_Streams_to_PubSub template. The actual build
input is the standalone Java source tree under src/; this file exists
so a reviewer can see at a glance what behaviour our pipeline adds
relative to the upstream template.

The customization is a single Filter step inserted between the change
stream source and the Pub/Sub sink: records whose every mod has
payload_link NULL on both sides are dropped; malformed records pass
through so the downstream reconciler / DLQ surface them.

If upstream's pipeline shape evolves and this reference diverges from
our src/ tree, regenerate the diff against a fresh clone of upstream
to keep the reference accurate. See README.md for the procedure. The
SHA in upstream.txt is the upstream commit this diff was last reviewed
against; the diff was verified to apply cleanly (`git apply --check`)
against that revision when captured.

